Thanks for fixing this [~lichangleo]. Can you also wrap each call in a {{isDebugEnabled()}} call. That way we don't incur the overhead of generating the log strings unless debug logging is turned on. e.g.

{code}
    if (NameNode.blockStateChangeLog.isDebugEnabled()) {
        NameNode.blockStateChangeLog.debug("BLOCK* Removing stale replica "
             + "from location: " + r.getExpectedStorageLocation());
    }
{code}
